headlines.description: — Tyler Herro scored 26 points in his return from a three-game absence with a bruised thigh, Duncan Robinson tied a season-high with 26 points and the Miami Heat rolled past the Indiana Pacers 125-96 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Herro, Robinson each score 26, Heat roll past Pacers 125-96

events.name: Detroit Pistons at New York Knicks

headlines.description: — Kemba Walker smiled his way around the court, finally in position to help the Knicks again in his hometown.
headlines.shortLinkText: Knicks beat Pistons 105-91 to end monthlong home woes

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Brandon Ingram had 28 points, Nickeil Alexander-Walker scored 22 of his 27 in the second half and the New Orleans Pelicans beat the Portland Trail Blazers 111-97 on Tuesday night for their first three-game winning streak of the season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ingram, Alexander-Walker shoot Pelicans past Blazers 111-97

headlines.description: — Jalen Brunson scored 26 points, Dorian Finney-Smith came alive in the second half and the Dallas Mavericks, with a boost from two newly signed players, defeated the Minnesota Timberwolves 114-102 in a battle of attrition Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brunson scores 26, replacements help Mavericks beat Wolves

events.name: Phoenix Suns at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Devin Booker continued to distance himself from a hamstring injury that cost him seven games, scoring 24 points with nine rebounds and seven assists as the Phoenix Suns earned a 108-90 victory Tuesday night over the Los Angeles Lakers.
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker, Ayton push Suns past Lakers 108-90
